Easy Interview Answer

What is SARIMAX?

SARIMAX (Seasonal AutoRegressive Integrated Moving Average with eXogenous Variables) is an advanced time series forecasting model that predicts future values using historical data, seasonality, trends, and external influencing variables such as holidays, prices, weather, or promotions.

Memory Trick
ARIMA
  ↓
SARIMA
  ↓
SARIMAX

ARIMA = Trend Forecasting

SARIMA = Trend + Seasonality

SARIMAX = Trend + Seasonality + External Factors

This is why SARIMAX is generally more powerful and often more accurate than SARIMA when relevant external variables are available.

